    {
      "id": "intro",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Irregular preterites at a glance",
      "body": "# The preterite - irregular verbs\n\nIn Lesson 13 you learned the regular preterite: *habl**é***, *habl**ó*** - with a written accent on the final syllable.\n\nBut the most common verbs are **irregular**. They have their own stem and - this is the big contrast - **no written accent** on the yo and él forms.\n\n| Verb | yo | él/ella |\n|---|---|---|\n| ir / ser | **fui** | **fue** |\n| hacer | **hice** | **hizo** |\n| tener | **tuve** | **tuvo** |\n\nCompare:\n\n- regular: *habl**é***, *habl**ó*** (with accent)\n- irregular: *fui*, *fue*, *hice*, *hizo*, *tuve*, *tuvo* (**no** accent)\n\nRemember: **never** write an accent on *fui*, *hice*, *hizo*, *tuve* or *tuvo*."
    },
    {
      "id": "step-ir-ser",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "ir = ser: the same forms",
      "body": "## ir and ser share the preterite\n\nThe two verbs *ir* (to go) and *ser* (to be) have **exactly the same forms** in the preterite:\n\n| Person | Form |\n|---|---|\n| yo | **fui** |\n| tú | **fuiste** |\n| él / ella | **fue** |\n| nosotros | **fuimos** |\n| vosotros | fuisteis |\n| ellos / ellas | **fueron** |\n\nContext decides which meaning applies:\n\n- ***Fui** a Madrid.* - I **went** to Madrid. (ir → motion, often with *a*)\n- *Ayer **fui** profesor por un día.* - Yesterday I **was** a teacher for a day. (ser → identity/profession)\n\nSo *fui* is ambiguous: \"I went\" or \"I was\". The sentence tells you which one."
    },
    {
      "id": "step-hacer-tener",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "hacer and tener",
      "body": "## hacer (to do/make)\n\n| Person | Form |\n|---|---|\n| yo | **hice** |\n| tú | **hiciste** |\n| él / ella | **hizo** |\n| nosotros | **hicimos** |\n| vosotros | hicisteis |\n| ellos / ellas | **hicieron** |\n\nWatch the spelling: yo = *hice* (with **c**), but él = *hi**z**o* (with **z**). The z keeps the soft sound before the *o*.\n\n## tener (to have)\n\n| Person | Form |\n|---|---|\n| yo | **tuve** |\n| tú | **tuviste** |\n| él / ella | **tuvo** |\n| nosotros | **tuvimos** |\n| vosotros | tuvisteis |\n| ellos / ellas | **tuvieron** |\n\nExamples:\n\n- ***Hice** la cena.* - I made dinner.\n- ***Tuve** un problema.* - I had a problem.\n\nNo accent on *hice*, *hizo*, *tuve* or *tuvo*."
    },
